%20a%20lawsuit%20to%20recover%20tariff%20payments%20imposed%20by%20the%20Trump%20administration.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20retailer%20challenged%20tariffs%20enacted%20under%20the%20International%20Emergency%20Economic%20Powers%20Act.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECostco%20is%20seeking%20a%20full%20refund%20of%20duties%20paid.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-new-hours-fees-changing-prices-tiers-customer-caste-system-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECostco%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20suing%20the%20government%20to%20recover%20tariff%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wholesale%20retailer%20has%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20US%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%20agency%2C%20and%20Rodney%20S.%20Scott%2C%20the%20Commissioner%20of%20US%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20asks%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-tariffs-blocked-federal-court-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20Court%20of%20International%20Trade%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20strike%20down%20tariffs%20imposed%20by%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20by%20executive%20order%20under%20the%20International%20Emergency%20Economic%20Powers%20Act%2C%20and%20to%20ensure%20tariff%20refunds%20for%20businesses%20that%20paid%20import%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20complaint%20submitted%20Friday%2C%20November%2028%2C%20the%20retailer%20said%20it%20is%20seeking%20a%20%26quot%3Bfull%20refund%26quot%3B%20of%20duties%20it%20paid%20after%20Trump%20used%20the%20emergency-powers%20law%20to%20levy%20what%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Breciprocal%26quot%3B%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20cited%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flead-plaintiff-in-case-against-trumps-tariffs-wine-improting-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprevious%20lawsuit%2C%20VOS%20Selections%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Inc.%20vs.%20Trump%2C%20filed%20against%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20for%20which%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20heard%20arguments%20in%20early%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20separate%20action%20is%20necessary%2C%20however%2C%20because%20even%20if%20the%20IEEPA%20duties%20and%20underlying%20executive%20orders%20are%20held%20unlawful%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20importers%20that%20have%20paid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-may-happen-next-court-strikes-down-trumps-ieepa-tariffs-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIEEPA%20duties%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20Plaintiff%2C%20are%20not%20guaranteed%20a%20refund%20for%20those%20unlawfully%20collected%20tariffs%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20their%20own%20judgment%20and%20judicial%20relief%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20complaint%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20complaint%20highlights%20a%20process%20called%20liquidation%2C%20which%20is%20when%20customs%20completes%20its%20final%20review%20and%20determines%20the%20official%20amount%20of%20duty%20for%20a%20particular%20shipment.%20Liquidation%20typically%20provides%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%20with%20the%20opportunity%20to%20either%20refund%20the%20importer%20or%20demand%20additional%20duties%20to%20be%20paid.%20This%20process%20must%20be%20completed%20within%20one%20year%20of%20a%20shipment's%20entry%20unless%20it%20is%20extended%20at%20the%20discretion%20of%20the%20CBP.%20It%20is%20unknown%20if%20a%20refund%20could%20happen%20once%20liquidation%20is%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20complaint%2C%20tariffs%20on%20Costco's%20imports%20will%20begin%20to%20be%20liquidated%20as%20early%20as%20December%2015%2C%20and%20the%20CBP%20has%20already%20declined%20the%20company's%20request%20to%20extend%20the%20liquidation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPlaintiff%20seeks%20relief%20from%20the%20impending%20liquidations%20to%20ensure%20that%20its%20right%20to%20a%20complete%20refund%20is%20not%20jeopardized%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20complaint%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20of%20International%20Trade%20and%20the%20District%20Court%20for%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20have%20both%20ruled%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fappeals-court-strikes-down-donald-trump-sweeping-tariff-plan-scotus-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIEEPA%20tariffs%20illegal%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20separate%20occasions.%20Their%20rulings%20are%20mostly%20based%20on%20the%20Constitution%2C%20which%20says%20that%20Congress%20has%20the%20exclusive%20power%20to%20levy%20taxes%20and%20collect%20duties.%20The%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20Federal%20Circuit%20reaffirmed%20the%20CTI's%20decision%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20the%20IEEPA%20for%20tariffs%20eventually%20made%20its%20way%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20and%20the%20court%20is%20currently%20deliberating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECostco%20did%20not%20specify%20the%20amount%20of%20duties%20it%20has%20paid%20in%20the%20complaint.%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Scott%20Bessent%20said%20in%20a%20filing%20submitted%20to%20SCOTUS%20in%20September%20that%20the%20government%20could%20end%20up%20owing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-could-owe-americans-if-scotus-overturns-tariffs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%241%20trillion%20in%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20should%20the%20court%20rule%20against%20the%20Trump%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-ceo-ron-vachris-career-timeline-earnings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECostco's%20CEO%2C%20Ron%20Vachris%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20during%20a%20Q2%20earnings%20call%2C%20%26quot%3BAbout%20a%20third%20of%20our%20sales%20in%20the%20US%20are%20imported%20from%20other%20countries%2C%20and%20less%20than%20half%20of%20those%20are%20items%20coming%20from%20China%2C%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Canada.%26quot%3B%20This%20was%20before%20Trump's%20April%202%20%26quot%3BLiberation%20Day%26quot%3B%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECostco%2